data.name: label40.Text
data.value: NOTE: When you launch FFmpeg Utilizer, it automatically creates the necessary default folders: Downloads, Output, tmp, and Tools, which are essential for the automation process. • The program will always download the stable essentials release of FFmpeg and FFplay from https://www.gyan.dev/ffmpeg/builds/. • If the download is interrupted or still in progress, the file will be stored in the tmp (Temporary) folder. • Once the download is complete, it will be moved to the Downloads folder for temporary storage. • After the file has been successfully moved, FFmpeg Utilizer will unpack it into a subfolder located in Tools, set the appropriate references to the respective tools, and save the settings. • Finally, once all the steps are completed, the downloaded file in the Downloads folder will be removed to clean up. Please note that download and unpacking speeds may vary depending on your location, the server's response time, and the speed of your internet connection.
